<div class="col two-sm last" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn2">
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<h3>Travel information</h3>
<p>Road information There is free disabled parking near all main entrances and in our main car parks. Please allow plenty of time to find a space.   Our car park is a pay and display system but spaces are limited so please allow plenty of time to park.   Bus information The nearest bus stop is on the Quay at Bideford</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<h3>Parking</h3>
<p>In the patient parking areas, there is a pay and display system which is clearly signposted.<br/>Drivers displaying a valid blue disability badge will be able to park in designated spaces at no charge. The pay and display charges are: <br/>•	Up to 2 hours		£1.80<br/>•	Up to 4 hours		£2.10<br/>•	Up to 24 hours	£4.10<br/><br/>Parking charges apply at all times. These can be paid by cash, phone or online. Details are clearly displayed on the tariff signs.</p>
